{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSBulletList","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/ContentDisplay"],"kind":"mentions"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Types","level":2,"text":"Types","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Three types are proposed:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unordered (by default)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Collects related items that don’t need to be in a specific order or sequence."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ordered"}]},{"text":": Collects related items with numeric order or sequence.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bare"}]},{"text":": An unordered list without any bullets or alphanumeric sequence.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Types can be mixed in list, but must be identical for the same "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSBulletList.NestedLevel"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Levels","level":2,"text":"Levels","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lists can include nested items to indicate hierarchy or subcategories, with indentation distinguishing each level."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Arrange ordered list items logically, such as ranking by importance, highest to lowest values, or in alphabetical \/ numeric order."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Three levels are maximum."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Text-Style","level":2,"text":"Text Style","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"List can be used with different font sizes:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Body Large"}]},{"type":"text","text":": If the text accompanying the list component is the Body Large text. This variant is designed for more visual, engaging experiences."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Body Medium"}]},{"text":": If the text accompanying the list component is the Body Medium text. This variant is best suited for functional, task-oriented experiences.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Cases-forbidden-by-design","level":2,"text":"Cases forbidden by design","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"it is not allowed to have a depth of items greater than 3","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Internationalisation-considerations","level":2,"text":"Internationalisation considerations","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For latin-based speaking countries, like France, Spain, United Kingdom or Belgium, the european “arabic” numbers are used for the first level of depth"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the ordered bullet list. For the second and third levels, the european alphabets are used with upper and lower case values."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However for countries speaking arabic, these rules can’t be applied. Indeed, there is no notion of upper and lower case characters in arabic alphabet."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In addition, the numbers in use (i.e. the european “arabic” numbers like “1, 2, 3”) are accepted in arabic countries, even if the “true arabic” numbers (like “ ٢ ٣ ١”) are used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in middle-east arabic countries and for official documents."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Thus the OUDS ordered bullet list will use “european” numbers for first level, and arabic alphabets for second and third levels."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Code-samples","level":2,"text":"Code samples","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["       \/\/ 1. Unordered list with bullets","       OUDSBulletList {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 1.1. Item of Unordered list with bullet as tick, a text style","       \/\/ body medium and text bold","       OUDSBulletList(type: .unordered(asset: .tick),","                      textStyle: .bodyMedium,","                      isBold: true)  {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 2. Bare list with 3 items","       OUDSBulletList(type: .bare) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 3. Ordered list with 3 items","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 3.1. Ordered list with 3 items in first level,","       \/\/ and one item as sub item (second level),","       \/\/ and 2 items as sub item in (third level)","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\") {","               OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1\") {","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.1\")","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.2\")","               }","           }","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ Same Bullet list but items in third level with free icon as bullet","       let icon = Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\")","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\") {","               OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1\", subListType: .unordered(asset: .icon(icon))) {","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.1\")","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.2\")","               }","           }","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","level":2,"text":"Design documentation","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-bullet-list"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","level":2,"text":"Themes rendering","type":"heading"},{"anchor":"Orange","level":3,"text":"Orange","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_bullet_list_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","level":3,"text":"Orange Compact","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_bullet_list_OrangeCompact"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Sosh","level":3,"text":"Sosh","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_bullet_list_Sosh"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Wireframe","level":3,"text":"Wireframe","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_bullet_list_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.0.0 (Figma component design version)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Version","type":"aside"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.2.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Since","type":"aside"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Bullet list is a UI element that helps to view in related individual text items grouped together; items usually starting with a number or a bullet.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Bullet list is also known as ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unordered list"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ordered list"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" and is not an interactive element by default.","type":"text"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"anchor":"Structures","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/Item"],"title":"Structures","generated":true},{"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/init(type:textStyle:isBold:items:)"],"title":"Initializers","generated":true},{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/body"],"title":"Instance Properties","generated":true},{"anchor":"Enumerations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/TextStyle","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/Type","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/UnorderedAsset"],"title":"Enumerations","generated":true},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSBulletList\/V